Day 3 — Debugging Thinking (Core Skill)
Rule #1: Errors are not problems — they are messages

Example:

print(name)

If name is not defined:

NameError: name 'name' is not defined

This tells you EXACTLY what went wrong.

Rule #2: Read errors from bottom to top

Most beginners read wrong direction.

Correct way:

Bottom line = actual error
Middle = location
Top = context
Rule #3: Print debugging

If something breaks:

print(variable)

This is your first tool.

